snippet.textDisplay:
You’ve got this!💪🏽
If you are struggling with...
-Axienty
-Depression
-bipolar
-bipolar depression
-And much much more
The list goes on and on.
You can do this.
You can push through.
You are enough.
You are allowed to take people’s thoughts about you seriously.
You are allowed to care what people think.
Do not let things creep down into you.
Think before you assume.
Here’s a little skit.

It involves 3 girls, and her friend. You will be doing Kaitlyns POV.
Annie: Whispers to Kia
Kia: Listens To Kia
Lauren: Asks to join in
They all discuss. But Kaitlyn is not asked to join.
They discuss about the party they will be throwing for her.
Kaitlyns Thoughts:
Omg, they probably hate me. There’s probably a stain on my shirt and i don’t know about it and there making fun of it, wait is there? Is there something wrong with my teeth? Are the laughing at me? Are they talking about ME? Am i being a good friend? Did i say something? Wait, i think i told her, shirt collar was messed up.. I HOPE THEY ARENT MAD. Do not have a panic attack, do not.
It happens.
But push through,
Take a walk🦵🏻
Take a run
Take a hot bath!😀
Take a long shower 🚿
Take a mental heath care day. (Where you eat what YOU WANT. No matter the calories, No matter the fat, No matter what any body else says. Where you pick your outfit, THAT YOU WANT TO WEAR. Not what the girl at school wants you too. Cook. Clean. Do your hair. Brush your teeth. Paint your nails. Work out. Show off your new outfit!)
Get an companion. (Like a puppy!)
It’s ok, to not be ok.

I was like ok. He then asked for my bank account number and I was like hell no. I told him that he should help homeless people and give some to the church. He then said ' dear you broke my heart'  I bursted out laughing 😂😂😂
